Covid 19 Timeline

In [1]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from datetime import date
import numpy as np
 
%matplotlib inline
In [2]:
# reference: https://www.yalemedicine.org/news/covid-timeline
dates = [date(2020, 1, 9), date(2020, 1, 21), date(2020, 1, 31), date(2020, 2, 3), date(2020, 3, 11), date(2020, 3, 19), date(2020, 4, 16), date(2020, 5, 28), date(2020, 6, 10), date(2020, 6, 26), date(2020, 7, 7), date(2020, 7, 16), date(2020, 7, 23), date(2020, 8, 3), date(2020, 8, 17), date(2020, 9, 15), date(2020, 9, 23), date(2020, 9, 25), date(2020, 9, 28), date(2020, 10, 8), date(2020, 10, 19), date(2020, 11, 5), date(2020, 11, 18), date(2020, 12, 21), date(2020, 12, 29)]
min_date = date(np.min(dates).year, np.min(dates).month, np.min(dates).day)
max_date = date(np.max(dates).year, np.max(dates).month, np.max(dates).day)
labels = ['WHO Announces Mysterious\n Coronavirus-Related\n Pneumonia\n in Wuhan, China', 'CDC Confirms\n First US\n Coronavirus Case', 'WHO Issues\n Global Health Emergency', 
          'US Declares\n Public Health Emergency', 'US Declares Public Health Emergency', ' California Issues\n Statewide Stay-at-Home Order', 'Gating Criteria Emerge as a Way\n to Reopen the Economy', 'US COVID-19 Deaths Pass the 100,000 Mark', 'US COVID-19 Cases Reach\n 2 Million', 'White House Coronavirus Task Force\n Addresses Rising Cases in\n the South', 'US Surpasses 3 Million Infections,\n Begins WHO Withdrawal', 'US Reports New Record\n of Daily COVID-19 Cases', 'Antibody Levels Drop\n After First 3 Months\n of COVID-19 Infection', 'New US Pandemic Phase;\n US to Pay Sanofi,\n GlaxoSmithKline $2B\n for Vaccine', 'COVID-19 Now is the Third-Leading\n Cause of Death in the US', 'CDC Reports on Spread of COVID-19\n at Restaurants', 'A New, More Contagious Strain\n of COVID-19 is Discovered', 'Midwest States See Increase in\n COVID-19 Cases', 'Global COVID-19 Deaths Surpass\n 1 Million', 'More Americans Trust Biden\n to Lead Health Care System', 'Global Cases Top 40 Million', 'Study Predicts Difficulties\n in Nationwide COVID-19 Immunity', 'Pfizer, BioNTech Vaccine\n is 95% Effective', 'New COVID-19 Variant\n Circling the UK', 'First US Case of New COVID-19\n Variant Found in Colorado']
labels = ['{0:%d %b %Y}:\n{1}'.format(d, l) for l, d in zip (labels, dates)]
levels = np.tile([-1.7, 1.5, -1, 1, -0.5, 0.5],
                 int(np.ceil(len(dates)/6)))[:len(dates)]
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20, 10), constrained_layout=True)
markerline, stemline, baseline = ax.stem(dates, levels,
                                         linefmt="C3-", basefmt="k-",
                                         use_line_collection=True)
plt.setp(markerline, mec="k", mfc="w", zorder=3)
markerline.set_ydata(np.zeros(len(dates)))
vert = np.array(['top', 'bottom'])[(levels > 0).astype(int)]
for d, l, r, va in zip(dates, levels, labels, vert):
    ax.annotate(r, xy=(d, l), xytext=(-3, np.sign(l)*3),
                textcoords="offset points", va=va, ha="center", fontfamily='monospace', fontweight='bold', color='black', fontsize=10)
ax.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
for spine in ["left", "top", "right"]:
    ax.spines[spine].set_visible(False)
ax.margins(y=0.1)
_ = ax.set_title('Important Milestones in the COVID-19 Pandemic', fontweight="bold", fontfamily='monospace', fontsize=16, 
                 color='royalblue')
plt.show()

Part 2: AQI of Regional Cities - Heat Maps New York City

In [1]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.colors import ListedColormap
import seaborn as sb
import random
%matplotlib inline
In [2]:
cbsa = pd.read_csv("daily_aqi_by_cbsa_2020.csv",index_col='Date',parse_dates=True)
In [3]:
ny = cbsa[cbsa["CBSA Code"]==35620]
df = ny.drop(columns=['CBSA','CBSA Code','Category','Defining Parameter','Defining Site','Number of Sites Reporting','Region'])
In [4]:
df['AQI'] = pd.to_numeric(df.AQI, errors='coerce')
df.dropna(inplace=True)
In [5]:
df_m = df.copy()
df_m['month'] = [i.month for i in df_m.index]
df_m['day'] = [i.day for i in df_m.index]
# group by month and year, get the average
df_m = df_m.groupby(['month', 'day']).mean()
In [6]:
df_m = df_m.unstack(level=0)
In [7]:
df_m.dropna(inplace=True)
In [9]:
# figure
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 12))
# plot heatmap
sb.heatmap(df_m, cmap=ListedColormap(['green', 'yellow', 'orange','red','maroon']), annot=True,vmin= 0, vmax=250, square=True,
           linewidth=0.3, cbar_kws={"shrink": 0.5}, fmt='g')
# xticks
ax.xaxis.tick_top()
xticks_labels = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun',
                'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']
plt.xticks(np.arange(12) + .5, labels=xticks_labels)
plt.yticks(rotation=0)
# axis labels
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('')
# title
title = 'nyc daily Air Quality Index\n2020'.upper()
plt.title(title, loc='left')
plt.show()
